Date: Fri, 20 Jun 2026 13:26:00 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] Fix getApi crash with null serverId on fresh browser load

When a user clears cookies and reloads, stored credentials contain a
server entry without an Id field (only ManualAddress). During
initialization, initApiClient() calls addApiClient(), which fires the
'apiclientcreated' event. The handler in ServerConnections.js calls
this.getApi(apiClient.serverId()), but serverId() returns undefined
because the server hasn't fetched /System/Info/Public yet.

getApi() passed the null serverId to getApiClient(), which threw
"item or serverId cannot be null" -- an uncaught exception that halted
all app initialization, leaving the user stuck on the loading logo.

Fix: Add a null guard to getApi() so it returns undefined gracefully.
All downstream callers already handle undefined return values with
guard clauses, allowing the app to continue initializing.

diff --git a/src/lib/jellyfin-apiclient/connectionManager.js b/src/lib/jellyfin-apiclient/connectionManager.js
index f156db8952..e2385891d7 100644
--- a/src/lib/jellyfin-apiclient/connectionManager.js
+++ b/src/lib/jellyfin-apiclient/connectionManager.js
@@ -820,6 +820,9 @@ export default class ConnectionManager {
      * @returns {import('@jellyfin/sdk').Api}
      */
     getApi(serverId) {
+        if (!serverId) {
+            return undefined;
+        }
         const apiClient = this.getApiClient(serverId);
         apiClient._sdk ??= toApi(apiClient);
         return apiClient._sdk;
